<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n11121k"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n11" href="#n11121k">N11 (VI.B.5)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n11all.htm#n11121k"> 121(k)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> jumble of history &amp; renegation / in Czd&apos;s street</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><b>Bassesses politiques</b> Ce sont les hommes de la r&eacute;publique et de l&apos;Empire qui salu&egrave;rent avec enthousiasme la Restauration. La conduite et l&apos;ingratitude des personnages &eacute;l&eacute;v&eacute;s par la r&eacute;volution furent abominables envers celui qu&apos;ils affectent aujourd&apos;hui de regretter et d&apos;admirer. ... vous, cr&eacute;atures de cet usurpateur, vous d&eacute;passiez en exag&eacute;ration les sentiments des royalistes. Les ministres, les grands dignitaires, pr&ecirc;t&egrave;rent &agrave; l&apos;envi serment &agrave; la l&eacute;gitimit&eacute;; toutes les autorit&eacute;s civiles et judiciaires faisaient queue pour jurer haine &agrave; la nouvelle dynastie proscrite, amour &agrave; la race antique qu&apos;elles avaient cent et cent fois condamn&eacute;e. <br><font color="green">[Political baseness: The Restoration was hailed with enthusiasm by the very men who had been made by the Republic and the Empire. The behaviour and ingratitude of the personages raised by the Revolution were abominable towards him they affect today to regret and admire ... You, the creatures of this usurper, outdid in exaggeration the feelings of the Royalists. The ministers, the dignitaries, vied with one another to swear allegiance to legitimacy; all civil and judicial authorities lined up to swear hatred to the new exiled dynasty, love to the ancient race they had condemned hundreds of time before.]</font> <small> Chateaubriand, <a name="CHBD" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#CHBD"><cite title="source">&OElig;uvres choisies illustr&eacute;es</cite></a> (1912) III, <i> M&eacute;moires d&apos;Outre-tombe.</i> 101-2</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
